Peru to Protect Pension Funds Before Handover, Peruano Says

-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 
2011-04-17T15:06:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-17/peru-to-protect-pension-funds-before-handover-peruano-says.html
Peru will take steps to protect the
assets of the nation’s private pension funds before President
 Alan Garcia  leaves office on July 28, El Peruano  reported ,
citing Finance Minister Ismael Benavides.  The government will draw up measures to protect the Andean
country’s banking system and stabilize the stock market and
currency, Benavides said, the state-owned newspaper said,
without providing details.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in Lima at 
 jquigley8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net  